<p>Sebastian Bender, currently &#8220;juniorprofessor&#8221; at the <a href="https://www.uni-goettingen.de/en/faculty+of+philosophy/3047.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">University of Göttingen</a>, will be moving to <a href="https://www.philosophie.lmu.de/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München</a> (LMU Munich), where he will be professor of early modern philosophy.<span id="more-54314"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-54315 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/bender-sebastian.png" alt="" width="365" height="386" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/bender-sebastian.png 653w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/bender-sebastian-284x300.png 284w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/bender-sebastian-400x423.png 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 365px) 100vw, 365px" /></p>
<p><a href="https://www.sebastianbender.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Professor Bender</a> works primarily on topics in early modern metaphysics, epistemology, and philosophy of mind. He is the author of <a href="https://www.degruyterbrill.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110454949/html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Leibniz&#8217; Metaphysik der Modalität</em></a> (2016), among other works, which you can learn more about <a href="https://www.sebastianbender.net/home/publications" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> and <a href="https://philpeople.org/profiles/sebastian-bender" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>He takes up his new position at LMU Munich in August, 2025.</p>
<p>(via <span class="qu" tabindex="-1" role="gridcell" translate="no"><span class="gD" data-hovercard-id="S.Hartmann@lmu.de" data-hovercard-owner-id="16">Stephan Hartmann)</span></span></p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/07/10/bender-from-gottingen-to-lmu-munich/">Bender from Göttingen to LMU Munich</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>